	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes.&nbsp;&nbsp;You should consider using weapons.  Depending on your level, Dalnir is a good choice since you can get batons and I believe a variation of a bo stick.  If you are not high enough for Dalnir, just use any blunt weapons you loot from mobs for now.  Warhammers tend to be the fastest for one hand blunt (in the non-magical category).  Try to use a cracked staff for 2hb.<br><br>The catch is, each time you gain a level, max out your hand to hand first and then switch to weapons.  If you get into trouble with the weapons, switch to H2H until you can switch back.  Depending on your level, where you fight, and what you can afford your weapon progression may look like rusty/tarnished to bronze to fine steel and by then you should either be high enough or have enough cash coming in to afford batons or other low end weapons from Kunark.<br><br>Just remember that H2H must come first, since you may often do corpse recovery naked or need your innate abilities to bail out a group while your weapon skills mature.  <br><br>As for armor...silk is nice, crescent isn't much better, just has stats.  By the time you reach 30, you should be looking for wearable gear featuring AC and resists.  This is the current "fashion" trend for us...<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
