	   <tr><td colspan=2>Assuming that U only have 1 weapon, which hand should it be in for maximum advancement of skills?&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, does this create the best offensive destruction (i.e. would it do more damage is placed in primary or secondary hand)?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=97137405414425></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97137405414425><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=97137405414425>RE: Wich hand should the 1HB be in?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=97137405414425#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 12th 2:07 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends on the weapon and what skill you want to raise. If you want to raise 1hb, the weapon should be placed in the main hand. Skill checks for weapons happen when you swing the thing, and the secondary hand only attacks when dual wield goes off--less than a quarter of the time at low levels, about 60% at lv 50. If you are working on h2h, put the blunt in secondary hand or ignore it entirely. Best offense is generally the best damage/delay in primary hand with good damage in secondary. The delay in the secondary hand usually doesn't matter, because the weapon generally recycles before dual wield fires again. Use your best wep in primary. If you have two weapons similar dmg/dly ratios, the higher damage one should go in your off hand. That way, when dual wield fires, the extra hit does lots of extra damage.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
