	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with above poster.&nbsp;&nbsp;I currently play a warrior, 20th levl, and I use either Bullsmasher or Langseax in primary, and Brazen Brass Kilij in secondary, since the Kilij's delay is often less than my Dual Wield's delay.  Even if I get DW to pop every other attack on the Bullsmasher, it's got a delay of 20, which doubled makes it 40.  The K's delay is 35, so it is ready to go half a second before it's needed.  Now, if your dual wield is insanely high, and so is your dex, making it proc more than half the time, then look into getting a pair of equal delay weapons, so you can take advantage of the extra attacks.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
